title: Ms. President, Hillary Clinton Newsweek.
subtitle: A picture showing Hillary Clinton on the cover of Newsweek under the title "Madam President" is real, but it is not evidence that the news outlet colluded with Clinton's campaign before the 2016 presidential election.
author: Dan Evon
vclaim: The newspaper "Madam President," which holds the slogan Newsweek wins Hillary Clinton, was announced in the presidential election before 8 November 2016.
